  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The intervention program &quot;Obeldicks light&quot; is developed for overweight children aged 8-16
      years. This intervention is gender - and age specific.

      The 6-month intervention is based on nutrition course, behaviour therapy and exercise
      therapy. The evaluation compromised quality of structure, process and results of the
      intervention. 300 participants in a randomised controlled group design will be evaluated at 4
      time points: baseline, end of intervention, 6 months after end of intervention and 12 months
      after end of intervention.Primary outcome measure is change of weight status as standard
      deviation score of BMI. Drop-outs will be interviewed to improve the intervention.
    </textblock>
